properties.publicTransport: Buses and light rail services are not running to Circular Quay. Buses are using stops at Martin Place and light rail services are running to and from Town Hall only. Visit transportnsw.info for more details on transport changes and to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Vivid Sydney returns for its 14th year to light up the city for 23 consecutive nights from Friday 24 May to Saturday 15 June from 6pm to 11pm each night. Motorists are encouraged to avoid travelling around Circular Quay and The Rocks during Vivid or to expect delays on local roads, particularly on weekends.

Roads in Circular Quay, The Rocks and Millers Point will close each night from 5pm with additional closures on Friday nights and weekends in the city and around Darling Harbour. Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect each night. 

KEY ROAD CLOSURES

Sundays and Monday Public Holiday 10 June

  • *CLOSED* 5pm – midnight: Hickson Rd to Pottinger St, Pottinger St, Lower Fort St, Windmill St, Merriman St, Rodens Lane and Loftus St. In Ultimo, Mary Ann St and Omnibus Lane will close. Roads in Circular Quay north of Bridge St including sections of George, Pitt, Young, Phillip and Loftus Streets. Near King St Wharf, Erskine St westbound from Clarence St to Sussex St and Kent St southbound from Margaret St to Erskine St is closed. In The Rocks, Harrington St southbound from Argyle St to Essex St, and Argyle St eastbound from Lower Fort St to Harrington St is closed.
  • *CLOSED* 5.30pm - midnight: Darling Dr between Pier St and Ultimo Rd, and Thomas St from Quay St
  • Cumberland St south of Essex St from 12pm - midnight and Circular Quay West at the Overseas Passenger Terminal from 3pm - midnight are also closed.

Managed access to some hotels and businesses around The Rocks and Circular Quay will be maintained by traffic controllers on-site throughout Vivid Sydney when safe to do so.

Special event clearway parking restrictions are in effect until midnight on various roads around Circular Quay, The Rocks and the Sydney CBD.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.
